{
  "texts": [
    "Subsequently, end-to-end improvement algorithms have emerged with considerable potential to narrow this gap, yielding higher-quality solutions.",
    "However, compared to construction algorithms, improvement algorithms are more time-consuming.",
    "As introduced in Section 3.2, the -OPT algorithm is a local search method used for TSP.",
    "The core concept involves removing edges from a feasible tour and attempting to reconnect the remaining segments to find a shorter path.",
    "This improvement process is iteratively performed to obtain a highquality solution."
  ]
}